<subSubSection box="[197,1003,731,758]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,152,912]" box="[197,1003,731,758]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,337,731,757]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Perez-Gelabert" authorityYear="2009" box="[414,478,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Efferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis box="[414,478,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for black, referring to the color of the tibiae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,152,912]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,323,770,796]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Perez-Gelabert" authorityYear="2009" box="[332,492,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Efferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis box="[332,492,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Efferia picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the mostly black vestiture of the body, brownish-yellow tomentum, mostly black mystax and palpi, face at antennae about 1/2 as wide as a compound eye, mostly or entirely black setose pleura, scattered black setae of the fore coxae, entirely black tibiae, and combined characters of the terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[486,630,886,912]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–57" captionStartId="31.[151,271,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[163,1431,293,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[151,1436,271,1907]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 52–57. Efferia picea sp. nov. Male terminalia, lateral view: 52. Intact, left side; 53. Gonostylus with thick sclerotization; 54. Phallus; and 55. Aedeagus with tubes and phallic flange. Female terminalia, lateral view: 56. Ovipositor; 57. Lateral spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455832/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Figs. 52–57</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
